text.tspan: The Hakka Board is a POV kit (Persistence of Vision) with an
ESP32-C3 (RISC-V) processor, 8 LEDs, and a shake sensor.
It uses the persistence of human vision and the afterimage effect:
when shaken, the LEDs rapidly turn on and off making text or
images appear to float in the air.
The board can do much more we are excited to see what
